{:source ["plugins/rama-skill/skills/rama/references/depot-reference.md" "plugins/rama-skill/skills/rama/references/depot-design.md"], :question "# Depot Partitioning\n\nWhat are Rama's depot partitioning strategies and when would you use each?\n\nWrite your answer to `answer.md` in this directory.", :extracted-at "2026-03-30T17:11:16.016001Z", :claims ["Rama depots support a random partitioning scheme using `:random` syntax that provides even distribution with no ordering guarantee." "Rama depots support hash-by-keyword partitioning using `(hash-by :field)` syntax that deterministically routes data by a map field." "Rama depots support hash-by-function partitioning using `(hash-by fn-var)` syntax that deterministically routes by an extracted value." "Rama depots support hash-by-identity partitioning using `(hash-by identity)` syntax that hashes the value itself." "Rama depots support a disallow partitioning scheme using `:disallow` syntax that causes client appends to throw an exception." "The `hash-by` function argument must be a keyword or a top-level var, not an `fn` literal." "Custom partitioners can be defined using `defdepotpartitioner` and then passed to `declare-depot`." "A custom partitioner receives `[data num-partitions]` and returns the target partition index." "Random partitioning provides no ordering guarantee across records." "Hash-by partitioning guarantees that records with the same key land on the same partition, providing local ordering." "The partition key should match the primary PState access pattern to enable colocated `local-transform>` and `local-select>` without repartitioning." "A mismatched partition key forces a `|hash` repartition, adding an extra network hop and breaking local ordering." "When multiple PStates have different keys, partition by the most write-intensive key and repartition for secondary indexes." "Global depots have a single partition on task 0 and are intended for low-throughput data only." "For global depots, the partitioner argument is irrelevant." "Global depots are declared with `(declare-depot setup *depot :random {:global? true})`." "Internal (disallow) depots reject client appends and are only writable from topology code via `depot-partition-append!`." "Output depots are used for cross-module data publishing." "Tick depots emit on time intervals and cannot be appended to by clients." "Tick depots emit on task 0; to trigger all tasks, follow with `(|all)`." "Mirror depots require explicit partition routing via `|hash$$` when appending from topology code." "Same-depot design is preferred when events require local ordering on the same entity." "Separate depots are preferred when events are logically independent, have different throughput profiles, or different ack requirements." "The `:all-after` stream retry mode preserves local ordering by replaying failed records and all subsequent records on the partition." "The `:none` stream retry mode provides at-most-once delivery and is suited for best-effort analytics."]}
